article.headline: Oral Roberts 85, Centenary 71
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green had 30 points and nine rebounds to lead Oral Roberts past Centenary 85-71 Thursday night. Green, a 6-foot-7 freshman forward, scored 17 points in the second half to help the Golden Eagles (12-4, 5-0 Mid-Continent Conference) pull away after trailing 38-37 at the half. Green was 11-of-14 from the field and 8-of-12 on free throws. Ken Tutt added 17 points for ORU while teammate Jonathan Bluitt had 11 points and 11 assists. Andrew Wisniewski scored 26 points, 19 in the first half, and Shawn Davis added 12 points to lead the Gents (7-7, 2-2 Mid-Con). Wisniewski opened the game with a trey and scored 14 points in the first 4:37 to propel Centenary to a 16-6 lead. During the next four minutes, ORU reeled off 11 straight points, capped by Eric Fowlkes' layup that gave the Golden Eagles a 17-16 advantage. Davis' basket with 30 seconds left capped a 6-0 roll that gave Centenary a one-point lead at intermission. In the first 3:23 of the second half, Green had eight points to spark a 12-2 run to give ORU a 49-40 lead. Centenary never got closer than seven points during the rest of the game. ORU made 20-of-25 free throws in the second half to seal its eighth straight victory, equaling its longest winning streak since the 1996-97 season. The Golden Eagles outrebounded Centenary 33-26.
